Governor Dapo Abiodun has given appointment to four persons in Ogun State, less than one year to the end of his tenure. They are: Mr Adeleye Joseph Ademola for Teaching Service Commission; Hon. Onadeko Onamusi for House of Assembly Service Commission; Princess Adesola Ayoola Elegbeji and Hon. Akinpelu Aina Nurudeen for Judicial Service Commission. Abiodun on Thursday, forwarded the names of the four nominees and their portfolios to the Ogun State House of Assembly. Acknowledging Abiodun’s request for confirmation of the four nominees for appointment as commissions’ members, the Speaker, Rt. Hon. Olakunle Oluomo, read his letter plenary. The nominees are to appear before the lawmakers for screening at a date to be announced.